# tool_calls.jsonl Schema
# .agents/sessions/templates/tool_calls.jsonl.schema
# Source: agentic_system_design.md §8.2, §7.2

Every line in sessions/<id>/tool_calls.jsonl is a JSON object:

{
  "ts":              "ISO-8601 timestamp",
  "session_id":      "sess_<ulid>",
  "task_id":         "task_<ulid>",
  "agent":           "agent role name",
  "tool":            "github | figma | terraform | k8s | sentry | database | browser | playwright",
  "operation":       "specific operation called (e.g., read_file, list_issues)",
  "inputs_hash":     "hash(tool+operation+sorted_inputs)",
  "permission_tier": 1,
  "approved_by":     "auto | user | <agent-role>",
  "cache_hit":       false,
  "cache_ttl":       3600,
  "duration_ms":     1240,
  "result_status":   "success | error | timeout | rate_limited",
  "error":           null
}

## Rules

- Append-only — never modify existing entries
- Every tool call logged, whether hit or miss
- cache_hit = true when result served from .agents/cache/
- duration_ms = 0 for cache hits (no network call)
- If rate_limited = true: result_status = "rate_limited", error = "429 Too Many Requests"
